ingredientsDesc:
MICROPLATE: strips coated with Mumps virus.
CONJUGATE: anti-human IgG monoclonal antibodies labelled with peroxidase, in phosphate buffer solution.
POSITIVE CONTROL: Dilueted human serum, at known concentration of anti-Mumps IgG, in phosphate buffer 0.01 mol/l containing BSA 1% and sodium azide 0.09%.
CONTROL CUT OFF: Diluted human serum, at known concentration of anti-Mumps IgG, in phosphate buffer 0.01 mol/l with BSA 1% and sodium azide 0.09%.
NEGATIVE CONTROL: Human serum not containing anti-Mumps IgG, in phosphate buffer 0.01 mol/l, with BSA 1% and sodium azide 0.09%.
SUBSTRATE: Tetramethylbenzidine and hydrogen peroxide stabilized in citrate buffer 0.05 mol/l.
DILUENT 50X: Protein solution conc. 50x with added phenol 0.05% and Bronidox 0.02%.
WASH BUFFER 10X: Phosphate buffered saline, concentrated 10 times; contains Brij 0.5%.
STOP SOLUTION: H2SO4 0.3mol/l.
